chin current chief economic advisor gary cohn european central bank president mario draghi former bank of canada governor and current governor of the bank of england mark carney and the current prime minister of australia malcolm turnbull in addition former goldman employees have headed the new york stock exchange the world bank and major banks such as citigroup and merrill lynch contents  history  –  –  –  initial public offering of goldman sachs     – subprime mortgage crisis  profiting from the  subprime mortgage crisis  creation of gsamp trust s  conversion to a bank holding company  reputation tarnished  tarp and berkshire hathaway investment   use of federal reserves emergency liquidity programs   acquisition of remainder of jbwere  shut down of global alpha hedge fund   acquisition of business from deutsche bank   apples  billion bond offering   twitter initial public offering   underwriting of grand parkway system toll revenue bond   purchase of australian loan portfolio from suncorp   setlcoin   establishment of gs bank   retirement plan technology acquisition   purchase of petróleos de venezuela bonds   current operations  investment banking  investing and lending  institutional client services  investment management  gs capital partners  corporate citizenship  goldman sachs global leaders program  climate change policies  employee contributions  goldman sachs gives  community teamworks  junior banker task force   women   small businesses  high school investment  social impact funds  social impact bonds  controversies and legal issues  role in the financial crisis of   sale of dragon systems to lernout  hauspie despite accounting issues  litigation regarding stock price manipulation  use of offshore tax havens  involvement in the european sovereign debt crisis  employees views  greg smith resignation letter   what happened to goldman sachs by steven mandis  lawsuit regarding boy club culture  advice to short california bonds underwritten by the firm  perso