ldman randomly selected the securities instead of specifically creating a hedge for its won book   bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis p    bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis pp –   nathaniel popper april   main st paid for wall st maneuvers los angeles times   wang marian april   banks pressured credit agencies then blamed them propublica   a b lucchetti aaron ng serena april   abacus deal as bad as they come the wall street journal   a b c whalen philip tan bhala kara goldman sachs and the abacus deal seven pillars institute   a b wilchins dan april   factbox how goldmans abacus deal worked april   reuters retrieved february   hedge fund manager john paulson tells goldman sachs in late  he wants to bet against risky subprime mortgages using derivatives the risky mortgage bonds that paulson wanted to short were essentially subprime home loans that had been repackaged into bonds the bonds were rated bbb meaning that as the home loans defaulted these bonds would be among the first to feel the pain   the  million has been described as rent for the abacus name bethany mclean joe nocera all the devils are here the hidden history of the financial crisis p  paulson knocked on goldmans door at a fortuitous moment the firm had begun thinking about abacusrenal strategies  by that he meant that goldman would rent—for a hefty fee—the abacus brand to a hedge fund that wanted to make a massive short bet  paulson paid goldman  million to rent the abacus name   goldmans misleading statement on aca reuters april   when goldman wrapped the supersenior tranche of the abacus deal it did so with abn amro a toobigtofail bank and not with aca abn amro then laid off that risk onto aca but was on the hook for all of it if aca went bust as of course it did   a b c securities and exchange commission vs goldman sachs  co  fabrice tourre complaint securities fraud pdf us securities and exchange commission april   retrieved april     thomas jr landon april   a routine deal became an  million mistake the new york times rbs royal bank of scotland became involved in abacus almost by accident bankers working in london for abn amro a dutch bank that was later acquired by rbs agreed to stand behind a portfolio of american mortgage investments that were used in the deal abn amro shouldered almost all of the risks for what in retrospect might seem like a small reward that  million when the housing market fell and abacus collapsed rbs ended up on the hook for most of the losses subscription required  sec charges goldman sachs with fraud in structuring and marketing of cdo tied to subprime mortgages press release us securities and exchange commission april     a b c goldman sachs makes further comments on sec complaint press release business wire april     corkery michael april   goldman responds again to sec complaint the wall street journal subscription required  salmon felix april   goldmans misleading statement on aca reuters   maguire tom april   cnbc on the goldman complaint  this is surreal justoneminutetypepadcom   pitt harvey april   the secs dangerous gamble the daily beast   goldman in the eye of the beholder the atlantic october     jones ashby april   goldman v sec its all about materiality the wall street journal subscription required  federal crisis inquiry report p  fiderer david may   the moral compass missing from the greatest trade ever the huffington post   zuckerman gregory april   inside paulsons deal with goldman daily beast retrieved february   scott eichel a senior bear stearns trader was among those at the investment bank who sat through a meeting with paulson but later turned down the idea he worried that paulson would want especially ugly mortgages for the cdos like a bettor asking a football owner to bench a star quarterback to improve the odds of his wager against the team either way he felt it would look improper  it didn