man sachs group inc is an american multinational finance company that engages in global investment banking investment management securities and other financial services including asset management mergers and acquisitions advice prime brokerage and securities underwriting services it also sponsors private equity funds is a market maker and is a primary dealer in the united states treasury security market goldman sachs also owns gs bank usa a direct bank goldman sachs was founded in  and is headquartered at  west street in lower manhattan new york city with additional offices in other international financial centers due to its involvement in securitization during the subprime mortgage crisis goldman sachs suffered during the  financial crisis and received a  billion investment from the united states department of the treasury as part of the troubled asset relief program a financial bailout created by the emergency economic stabilization act of  the investment was made in november  and was repaid in june  the list of former employees of goldman sachs who moved on to government positions includes former us secretaries of the treasury robert rubin and henry paulson current united states secretary of the treasury steven mnuchin current chief economic advisor gary cohn european central bank president mario draghi former bank of canada governor and current governor of the bank of england mark carney and the current prime minister of australia malcolm turnbull in addition former goldman employees have headed the new york stock exchange the world bank and major banks such as citigroup and merrill lynch contents  history  –  –  –  initial public offering of goldman sachs     – subprime mortgage crisis  profiting from the  subprime mortgage crisis  creation of gsamp trust s  conversion to a bank holding company  reputation tarnished  tarp and berkshire hathaway investment   use of federal reserves emergency liquidity programs   acquisition of remainder of jbwere  shut down of global alpha hedge fund   acquisition of business from deutsche bank   apples  billion bond offering   twitter initial public offering   underwriting of grand parkway system toll revenue bond   purchase of australian loan portfolio from suncorp   setlcoin   establishment of gs bank   retirement plan technology acquisition   purchase of petróleos de venezuela bonds   current operations  investment banking  investing and lending  institutional client services  investment management  gs capital partners  corporate citizenship  goldman sachs global leaders program  climate change policies  employee contributions  goldman sachs gives  community teamworks  junior banker task force   women   small businesses  high school investment  social impact funds  social impact bonds  controversies and legal issues  role in the financial crisis of   sale of dragon systems to lernout  hauspie despite accounting issues  litigation regarding stock price manipulation  use of offshore tax havens  involvement in the european sovereign debt crisis  employees views  greg smith resignation letter   what happened to goldman sachs by steven mandis  lawsuit regarding boy club culture  advice to short california bonds underwritten by the firm  personnel revolvingdoor with us government  former new york fed chairmans ties to the firm  insider trading cases  rajat kumar insider trading case  stub month and allegedly misleading results in december   bonuses paid to employees in  despite financial crisis  benefits from the government bailout of aig  firms response to criticism of aig payments  september   meetings at the new york federal reserve   million settlement for massachusetts subprime mortgages   abacus mortgagebacked cdos and  million settlement    sec civil fraud lawsuit  tourre defense of abacus lawsuit  senate report on the causes of the financial crisis of   alleged commodity price manipulation  goldman sachs commodity index and the – food bubble  aluminum price and supply  oil futures sp