ing businesses trade at an enterprise valuetoebitda multiple of  times compared to  times for their global peers says the broker goldman sachs has added bharat petroleum in which is rated buy to its conviction list heres why its so bullish on the stock which has a price target of inr a share bpcl shares have lagged peer indian oil marketing companies omcs by  in the last  months driven by weaker than expected earnings in the last  quarters due to kochi startup costs however we believe this underperformance will reverse in next  months as  refining earnings pick up from hfye given ongoing kochi upgradeexpansion and  omc multiples rerate higher as investors give more credit for diminishing regulatory headwinds move towards dailydynamic pricing structurally rising retail volume growth with optionality of higher marketing margins longerterm goldman sachs also upgraded hindustan petroleum in to buy from neutral the broker which has a sumofthepartsbased price target of inr a share reckons the multiple for the fuel retailing business could rerate on less regulatory headwinds rising volume growth and possibility of higher marketing margins we upgrade hpcl to buy from neutral with  potential upside to our  revised month sotpbased target price of rs from rs we like hpcl’s exposure to the fuel retailing business highest amongst the omcs as of fy and it also has the highest sensitivity to changes in marketing margins and changes in valuation multiple for the marketing business where it has the highest ebitda contribution bharat petroleum last traded down  to inr a share while hindustan petroleum was up  to inr a share text size regular medium large gas goldman sachs oil refining retailing india most popular why altria is tanking starbucks when good stocks go bad  mindboggling stats on jeff bezos’ wealth att ups bond sale to  billion third biggest deal ever why bristolmyers is tanking latest in asiastocks blog latest in asiastocks blog join nowsign incustomer centermembershiptoo